From: CJ Damsleth <kim@damsleth.no>
Subject: [PATCH] usb: dwc3-apple: add apple,force-host-mode for PD-less host ports

The M4 generation (t6040/t8132) has no AP-visible USB-PD controller, so the
role-switch/typec cable event that dwc3-apple waits on to select host or device
mode never arrives; the core stays in DWC3_APPLE_PROBE_PENDING forever. The
existing apple,force-device-mode brings the core up in device mode at probe for
a permanently-tethered gadget port. Add the symmetric apple,force-host-mode so a
fixed downstream port (an external USB2 disk or hub carrying the Linux root, when
internal NVMe is unavailable) enumerates with no cable event.

Bring-up only: pairs with dr_mode="host". Do not submit as-is.

Signed-off-by: CJ Damsleth <kim@damsleth.no>
---
diff --git a/drivers/usb/dwc3/dwc3-apple.c b/drivers/usb/dwc3/dwc3-apple.c
index 5da4796b51c9..fd0299870bbc 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/dwc3/dwc3-apple.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/dwc3/dwc3-apple.c
@@ -493,6 +493,22 @@ static int dwc3_apple_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 					     "Failed forced device-mode init\n");
 	}
 
+	/*
+	 * t6040 external-root bring-up: the M4 generation has no AP-visible
+	 * USB-PD controller, so no typec cable event will ever arrive to select
+	 * host mode either. For a fixed downstream port (external USB2 disk or
+	 * hub carrying the Linux root), bring the core up in host mode
+	 * immediately so the device enumerates with no cable event.
+	 */
+	if (device_property_read_bool(dev, "apple,force-host-mode")) {
+		mutex_lock(&appledwc->lock);
+		ret = dwc3_apple_init(appledwc, DWC3_APPLE_HOST);
+		mutex_unlock(&appledwc->lock);
+		if (ret)
+			return dev_err_probe(&pdev->dev, ret,
+					     "Failed forced host-mode init\n");
+	}
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
